		<div id="post-4220" class="cf post-4220 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

			<h1>
				<a href="http://werblog.com/2013/02/twitter-updates-2013-02-08-to-2013-02-14/" title="Twitter Updates: 2013-02-08 to 2013-02-14" rel="bookmark">Twitter Updates: 2013-02-08 to 2013-02-14</a>
				
			</h1>

			<div class="post-footer">
				15 Feb 2013 &nbsp;&nbsp;| <a href="http://werblog.com/category/uncategorized/">Uncategorized</a>
				
			</div>

			<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
				<ul class="ws_tweet_list">
<li class="ws_tweet">Word. MT <a href="http://twitter.com/gigibsohn">@gigibsohn</a>: FCC Chief of Staff Zac Katz: transition to IP doesn&#039;t automatically mean that there is competition. <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23siliconflatiron">#siliconflatiron</a>s <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/300702583666929666">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">TIRED: net neutrality. WIRED: IP interconnection. <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23fakesiliconflat">#fakesiliconflat</a>irons <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/300732221080346626">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">TIRED: wireless. WIRED: unlicensed wireless. <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23fakesiliconflat">#fakesiliconflat</a>irons <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/300776376414375937">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Brilliantly written but misguided <a href="http://twitter.com/zunguzungu">@zunguzungu</a> reply to <a href="http://twitter.com/chirky">@chirky</a> on MOOCs. Reverses theoretical and practical. <a href="http://t.co/MS5BPIpP" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/MS5BPIpP</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301382968772018177">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">This is the kind of dangerously unrealistic and unreflective MOOCtopianism we should all be fighting: <a href="http://t.co/1Hu0TeqY" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/1Hu0TeqY</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301409337107169280">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Detailed report on the 1st Duke MOOC. One finding: &gt;600 hours of effort involved, including &gt;420 by the professor. <a href="http://t.co/EG12ZMZJ" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/EG12ZMZJ</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301507448513122304">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">I estimated more like 200-300 hours to do my <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification12">#gamification12</a> MOOC, but I didn&#039;t keep a detailed record. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301507836771450881">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">All kidding aside, it&#039;s an important point that MOOCs will grow because faculty will do lots of work for free or little money. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301514991251640320">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">OK, time to <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23STFU">#STFU</a> to watch the <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23SOTU">#SOTU</a>. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301515194230779905">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">RT <a href="http://twitter.com/adamwerbach">@adamwerbach</a>: Obama Cries Out for Climate-Change Solutions, but What Happens Now? &#8211; Atlantic Mobile <a href="http://t.co/4h8gurn9" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/4h8gurn9</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301692007879933952">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Great example why we need shared-by-default spectrum policy: assumed exclusivity creates scarcities. <a href="http://t.co/aq9JMHxk" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/aq9JMHxk</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301701902779965442">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Crazy. Does any other product move that many units? MT <a href="http://twitter.com/erickschonfeld">@erickschonfeld</a>: Gartner says mobile phone sales down 1.7% to 1.75 billion in 2012. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301702540238675968">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">&quot;The president also made an exaggerated claim of bipartisanship [because Romney flip-flopped].&quot; Isn&#039;t that the issue? <a href="http://t.co/1UGH4i3V" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/1UGH4i3V</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301705721689567233">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">A big confusion in the higher ed reform debate is the confusion of price, cost, and quality. Not the same at all. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301712479313068032">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Haven&#039;t used, but I&#039;m all for OS options!  MT <a href="http://twitter.com/LaCaraB">@LaCaraB</a>: can you help us spread our humble MOOC open source platform? <a href="http://t.co/h5rwVzvh" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/h5rwVzvh</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301723444029030401">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">My brother <a href="http://twitter.com/adamwerbach">@adamwerbach</a> plans to be arrested today protesting the Keystone XL pipeline: <a href="http://t.co/UgXtvFQv" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/UgXtvFQv</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301729699669889025">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Wow. Time to short telecom and get into the noodle biz!  RT <a href="http://twitter.com/trengriffin">@trengriffin</a>: About 95B packages,of instant ramen are sold per year. . <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301732286020321280">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet"><a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a>, the next session of my free open Gamification course on Coursera, launches April 1! <a href="http://t.co/jeq64wGB" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/jeq64wGB</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301760150061056000">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Thanks for all the <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a> retweets! Again, it starts up April 1 (and that&#039;s not a joke!). <a href="http://t.co/jeq64wGB" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/jeq64wGB</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301808469042941952">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Doesn&#039;t even mention the legal dream team! MT <a href="http://twitter.com/StevenOverly">@StevenOverly</a>: Neustar, most influential company you&#039;ve never heard of: <a href="http://t.co/Y7ilEL8p" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/Y7ilEL8p</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/301811193000108033">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">HBS folks: Is it true your faculty no longer teaches accounting, as <a href="http://twitter.com/claychristensen">@claychristensen</a> says here? <a href="http://t.co/7IChoLCf" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/7IChoLCf</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302050568862572545">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">For those who asked, my <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23Gamification13">#Gamification13</a> MOOC is an updated version of the Fall course; not a sequel. Register at: <a href="http://t.co/jeq64wGB" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/jeq64wGB</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302117501788098560">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Thx! RT <a href="http://twitter.com/umairh">@umairh</a>: Awesome -&gt; RT <a href="http://twitter.com/kwerb">@kwerb</a>: My <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23Gamification13">#Gamification13</a> MOOC is an updated version of the Fall course. Register at: <a href="http://t.co/jeq64wGB" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/jeq64wGB</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302120731519623168">-&gt;</a></li>
</ul>

				
			</div>

			
			


